{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "21", "m": "07", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "04", "M": "56", "S": "20"}}, "news": [{"title": "Surcharge on property transactions likely as Jharkhand government eyes revenue boost for civic bodies", "para": "Jharkhand's government plans a new ten percent surcharge on property transfers. This levy aims to increase revenue for municipal bodies across the state. The proposed surcharge will apply to stamp duty and registration fees for property sales. Funds collected will support civic bodies' revenue and capital expenditures. Public feedback on the draft rules is open until July twenty-fourth.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/jharkhand-government-proposes-10-surcharge-on-property-transactions-to-boost-civic-revenue/132527706?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-345909/132527706.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Telangana launches Indiramma housing scheme for poor in Hyderabad Core Urban Region", "para": "The Telangana government has launched the Indiramma housing scheme for the poor. This initiative will provide one lakh houses in Hyderabad's Core Urban Region. Each flat will have a built-up area of 525 square feet. Beneficiaries will receive a Rs 5 lakh subsidy from the government. The scheme aims to construct multi-storey buildings for eligible citizens.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/telangana-unveils-indiramma-housing-scheme-for-urban-poor-in-hyderabad/132527396?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-1662647/132527396.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "MahaRERA recovery warrant dashboard not updated for six months, activists question transparency", "para": "Consumer activists question MahaRERA's transparency regarding it